            <fr:title text="Singleton induction">Singleton induction</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0016.agda" type="external">erct-0016.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link> type with centre <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>. For any family of types <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\colon  A \to  \mathsf {Type}]]></fr:tex>, we may define a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\colon  B a \to  \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x : A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x : A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x : A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x : A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}Bx]]></fr:tex> satisfying <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,a = b]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>19</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-0016/0</fr:addr><fr:route>http://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0016/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi _x \colon  a = x]]></fr:tex> be the witness of contraction for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex>. Given <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b : Ba]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex>, we define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,x : Bx]]></fr:tex> by transporting <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> along the identification <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi _a^{-1} \cdot  \chi _x \colon  a = x]]></fr:tex>:</html:p>

  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,x :\equiv 
    
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _a^{-1}\cdot \chi _x\right \rparen \mathclose {}
_* b
  ]]></fr:tex>

  <html:p>Then we compute <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {ind}_{A,a}\,b\,a \equiv  
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \chi _a^{-1}\cdot \chi _a\right \rparen \mathclose {}
_* b  = \mathsf {refl}_*b = b]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
